{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Complex of game sports | image = | nickname = | former_names = | location = Olympic Complex, [[Ashgabat]], [[Turkmenistan]] | built = 2015 | opened = 2016 | operator = [[Government of Turkmenistan]] | surface = | architect = [[Polimeks]] | tenants = | seating_capacity = 15,000 }} The '''Complex of game sports''' ({{Lang-tk|Sportuň oýun görnüşleriniň toplumy}}) is an [[indoor arena]] located in [[Olympic Complex]], [[Ashgabat]], [[Turkmenistan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ashgabat2017.gov.tm/en/page/Oyunlar-Olimpiya-sahercesi|title=Olympic Complex|publisher=}}</ref> It is owned and operated by [[Government of Turkmenistan]] for [[2017 Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games]]. It has a seating capacity of 15,000 for concerts, for the sports like [[basketball]], volleyball, handball, badminton, modern rhythmic gymnastics and artistic gymnastics, fencing, table tennis, trampoline tumbling, judo and wrestling.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ashgabat2017.gov.tm/en/page/Oyunlar-Olimpiya-shaherchesi-15000-Tomashachylyk-usti-yapyk-arena|title=Complex of game sports|publisher=}}</ref>
== Structure of the building == The building has a universal arena 70m х 40 m.
