{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}} {{Use British English|date=May 2015}} {{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Burton-on-Trent Cricket Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Burton-on-Trent]], [[Staffordshire]] | establishment = 1840 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1840-1841 | club1 = [[North of England cricket team|North]] | date = 15 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/367.html Ground profile }}
'''Burton-on-Trent Cricket Ground''' (exact name unknown) was a [[cricket]] ground in [[Burton-on-Trent]], [[Staffordshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1840, when the [[North of England cricket team|North]] played the [[Marylebone Cricket Club]] in the grounds first [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match. The following year the ground held its second and final first-class match when the North again played the Marlybone Cricket Club.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/367_f.html First-Class matches played on Burton-on-Trent Cricket Ground]</ref>
The final recorded match on the County Ground came in 1848 and saw Burton-on-Trent play [[Manchester Cricket Club]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/367_misc.html Other matches played on Burton-on-Trent Cricket Ground]</ref> The exact location of the ground remains unknown, although some sources such as [[Cricinfo]] believe the ground may in fact be the Town Ground.
