{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{Use British English|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox cricketer | name = | image = | country = England | fullname = David Walker Lyon | nickname = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1943|7|2|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Douglas, Isle of Man|Douglas]], [[Isle of Man]] | heightft = | heightinch = | batting = Right-handed | bowling = Right-arm [[Fast bowling|fast-medium]] | role = | family = [[Andrew Lyon]] (brother) | club1 = [[Cambridgeshire County Cricket Club|Cambridgeshire]] | year1 = 1965&ndash;1972 | clubnumber1 = | deliveries = balls | columns = 1 | column1 = [[List-A cricket|List A]] | matches1 = 1 | runs1 = 0 | bat avg1 = &ndash; | 100s/50s1 = &ndash;/&ndash; | top score1 = 0[[not out|*]] | deliveries1 = 72 | wickets1 = 1 | bowl avg1 = 44.00 | fivefor1 = &ndash; | tenfor1 = &ndash; | best bowling1 = 1/44 | catches/stumpings1 = &ndash;/&ndash; | date = 23 July | year = 2010 | source = http://www.cricinfo.com/ci/content/player/233177.html Cricinfo }} {{Other uses|David Lyon (disambiguation){{!}}David Lyon}}
'''David Walker Lyon''' (born 2 September 1943) is a former English [[cricket]]er. Lyon was a right-handed [[batsman (cricket)|batsman]] who bowled right-arm [[Fast bowling|fast-medium]]. He was born at [[Douglas, Isle of Man|Douglas]], [[Isle of Man]].
Lyon made his debut for [[Cambridgeshire County Cricket Club|Cambridgeshire]] in the 1965 [[Minor Counties Championship]] against [[Bedfordshire County Cricket Club|Bedfordshire]]. From 1965 to 1972, he represented the county in 15 Minor Counties matches, with his final appearance coming against Bedfordshire.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/34/34726/Minor_Counties_Championship_Matches.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played by David Lyon]</ref>
Lyon also represented Cambridgeshire in a single [[List A cricket]] match against [[Buckinghamshire County Cricket Club|Buckinghamshire]] in the [[1972 Gillette Cup]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/34/34726/List_A_Matches.html List-A Matches played by David Lyon]</ref> In his only List-A match, he took a single wicket at a [[bowling average]] of 44.00, with best figures of 1/44.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/34/34726/a_Bowling_by_Team.html List A Batting and Fielding For Each Team by David Lyon]</ref>
His brother, [[Andrew Lyon|Andrew]], played List A cricket for Buckinghamshire and [[Middlesex County Cricket Club|Middlesex]].
