{{Infobox venue | name = Gol Gohar Sport Complex | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = Gol Gohar Sport Complex | former_names = | location = [[Sirjan]], Iran <!--Location, not address--> | coordinates = | built = 2015 | opened = 2015 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Gol Gohar Cultural and Sport Club|Gol Gohar]] | operator = [[Gol Gohar Cultural and Sport Club|Gol Gohar]] | surface = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 3,200 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = {{convert|105|x|68|m|abbr=on}} | scoreboard = | acreage = | website = http://gegsc.com/ | tenants = [[Gol Gohar F.C.|Gol Gohar]] (2015–present) }} '''Gol Gohar Sport Complex''' is the own sports complex of [[Gol Gohar Cultural and Sport Club]] based in [[Sirjan]], [[Iran]]. The sports complex includes sports halls, an indoor swimming pool and a football stadium.<ref>http://gegsc.com/index.php/%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B2%D8%AF%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%87%DB%8C%D8%A6%D8%AA-%D9%87%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%B2%D8%B4%DB%8C-%D8%B3%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86-%DA%86%D9%86%D8%AF-%D9%85%D9%86%D8%B8%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%87-%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B9%D9%87-%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%B2%D8%B4%DB%8C-%DA%AF%D9%84-%DA%AF%D9%87%D8%B1</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.persianfootball.com/forums/showthread.php?114152-The-most-modern-stadium-in-Iran-is-located-in../page21|title=The most modern stadium in Iran is located in.. - Page 21|publisher=}}</ref> The stadium is able to hold 3,200 people<ref>http://90tv.ir/news/414113/%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B2%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%82%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%84-%D9%88-%DA%AF%D9%84-%DA%AF%D9%87%D8%B1-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%B2%D8%B4%DA%AF%D8%A7%D9%87-3200-%D9%86%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%87-%D9%81%D9%82%D8%B7-2500-%D8%A8%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%AA-%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%AE%D8%AA%D9%87-%D9%85%DB%8C%D8%B4%D9%88%D8%AF</ref>. It is the home venue of [[Gol Gohar F.C.|Gol Gohar Football Club]].
