{{Infobox stadium | name = Bafoussam omnisports stadium | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Bafoussam]], [[Cameroon]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = 2014 | built = 2015 | opened = 2016 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Fédération Camerounaise de Football]] | operator = | surface = Grass | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = [[China National Machinery and Equipment Import and Export Corporation|CMEC]] | main_contractors = | capacity = 20,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = 68×105m | acreage = | tenants = }}
'''Bafoussam omnisports Stadium''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in Kouekong, a suburb of [[Bafoussam]], [[Cameroon]]. It is used mostly for [[association football|football]] matches and it also has athletics facilities. The stadium has seats for 20,000 people. It was built in 2015 and inaugurated on April 30, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://crtv.cm/fr/latest-news/sport-11/bafoussam-omnisports-stadium-inaugurated-17110.htm|title=Bafoussam Omnisports Stadium inaugurated}}</ref> It will also host some matches during the [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations]].
