{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=September 2018}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Rajinder Singh Institute Ground | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = Rajinder Singh Institute Ground | former names = | location = [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = 1994 | built = | opened = 1984 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Rajinder Singh Institute]] | operator = [[Rajinder Singh Institute]] | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 5,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = [http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/ground/57899.html Cricinfo] | publictransit = }} '''Rajinder Singh Institute Ground''' is a multi purpose stadium in [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]]. The ground is mainly used for organizing matches of football, cricket and other sports. The stadium has hosted nine [[Ranji Trophy]] matches <ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/908_f.html First-class matches]</ref> from 1964 when [[Karnataka cricket team]] played against [[Kerala cricket team]]<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/61/61711.html Scorecard]</ref> until 2008.
The stadium has hosted six [[List A]] matches <ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/908_a.html List A matches]</ref> in 1996 when [[Karnataka cricket team]] played against [[Kerala cricket team]]<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/61/61708.html Scorecard]</ref> until 2012 but since then the stadium has hosted non-first-class matches.<ref> [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/908_misc.html Other matches]</ref>
