[[File:Kaka samba d or.jpg|230px|thumb|alt=Kaká received 2008 Samba Gold in Milanello|[[Kaká]] received 2008 Samba Gold in [[Milanello]]]] The '''"Samba Gold"''' (Samba d'Or) is a [[association football|football]] award given to the best [[Brazil]]ian footballer in [[Europe]], as awarded by the Sambafoot Company. The inaugural award was made in 2008. The Samba Gold is determined by three voter panels: journalists, fellow footballers and votes from [[Internet]] users.
==History== * In 2008, the winner was [[A.C. Milan|Milan]] midfielder [[Kaká]]. [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]'s [[Robinho]] and [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]]'s [[Luís Fabiano]] placed second and third in voting, respectively. There were 30 nominations. Voting took place from 1 December till 30 December. Kaká obtained 25.03% of the vote, with 14.34% for Robinho and 13.65% for Fabiano.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sambafoot.com/en/news/11497_2008_samba_gold_results.html|title=2008 Samba Gold results - Sambafoot.com, all About Brazilian Football|website=www.sambafoot.com}}</ref> * In 2009, Luís Fabiano (20.91%) of Sevilla won the trophy ahead of [[Júlio César (football goalkeeper, born 1979)|Júlio César]] (17.58%) and Kaká (16.35%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sambafoot.com/en/news/15244_2009_samba_gold_results.html|title=2009 Samba Gold Results - Sambafoot.com, all About Brazilian Football|website=www.sambafoot.com}}</ref> * In 2010, the prize was awarded to [[Maicon Sisenando|Maicon]] (12.60%) from [[Inter Milan]] running ahead of [[Hernanes]] (10.76%) and [[Thiago Silva]] (9.56%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sambafoot.com/en/news/18131_2010_Samba_Gold_Results.html|title=2010 Samba Gold Results - Sambafoot.com, all About Brazilian Football|website=www.sambafoot.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inter.it/aas/news/reader?N=35765&L=en|title=Maicon wins Samba d'Or 2010|website=FC Internazionale - Inter Milan}}</ref> * In 2011, Milan defender [[Thiago Silva]] (16.33%) won the award ahead of [[Dani Alves]] from [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] (15.56%) and [[Hulk (footballer)|Hulk]] from [[FC Porto|Porto]] (14.41%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sambafoot.com/en/news/27312_thiago_silva__winner_of_the_samba_gold_trophy_2011.html|title=Thiago Silva: Winner of the Samba Gold trophy 2011 - Sambafoot.com, all About Brazilian Football|website=www.sambafoot.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sambafoot.com/en/news/27315_samba_gold__the_results.html|title=Samba Gold: The Results - Sambafoot.com, all About Brazilian Football|website=www.sambafoot.com}}</ref> * In 2012, the list of 30 candidates was announced on 26 November.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sambafoot.com/en/news/39340_the_samba_gold_trophy_2012__the_30_nominees.html|title=The Samba Gold Trophy 2012: The 30 nominees - Sambafoot.com, all About Brazilian Football|website=www.sambafoot.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sambafoot.com/en/news/39588_who_will_win_the_samba_gold_2012_.html|title=Who will win the Samba Gold 2012? - Sambafoot.com, all About Brazilian Football|website=www.sambafoot.com}}</ref> [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] [[Defender (association football)|defender]] Thiago Silva (17.70%) was awarded the 2012 Samba Gold on 31 December, edging out [[Ramires]] (17.04%) and [[Willian (footballer)|Willian]] (10.19%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sambafoot.com/en/news/40955_thiago_silva_retains_the_samba_gold_trophy_2012.html|title=Thiago Silva retains the Samba Gold Trophy 2012 - Sambafoot.com, all About Brazilian Football|website=www.sambafoot.com}}</ref> * In 2013, Thiago Silva won for a third consecutive year, beating [[Dante (footballer)|Dante]] and [[Oscar (footballer, born 1991)|Oscar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sambafoot.com/en/news/55282_thiago_silva_is_the_2013_samba_gold_winner.html|title=Thiago Silva is the 2013 Samba Gold Winner - Sambafoot.com, all About Brazilian Football|website=www.sambafoot.com}}</ref> * In 2014, [[Neymar]] won the award for the first time ever with a record percentage of votes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sambafoot.com/en/news/67568_neymar_wins_his_first_samba_gold.html|title=Neymar wins his first Samba Gold - Sambafoot.com, all About Brazilian Football|website=www.sambafoot.com}}</ref> * In 2015, Neymar won the award for the second consecutive years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sambafoot.com/en/news/78737_neymar_wins_the_samba_gold_for_the_second_consecutive_year__.html|title=Neymar wins the Samba Gold for the second consecutive year ! - Sambafoot.com, all About Brazilian Football|website=www.sambafoot.com}}</ref> * In 2016, [[Philippe Coutinho|Coutinho]] won the award for the first time, ending [[Neymar]]'s two year reign. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sambafoot.com/en/news/85738_philippe_coutinho_wins_the_samba_gold_2016.html|title=Philippe Coutinho wins the Samba Gold 2016|last=Stillman|first=Tim|date=December 31, 2016|website=Sambafoot|publisher=Sambafoot|access-date=December 31, 2016}}</ref>
==Winners==
